<Author>dannes
<Content>Fantastic Location We recently stayed at the Hotel Lourve forum, and found it a great location to easily catch the metro or walk to the Lourve, Notre Dame, and The Siene (an easy 5-10min walk). The room we stayed in was the smallest on our European trip, however it didnt really bother us. The shower however was very small, and I did burn myself trying to turn around. There is a lift to use which will hold 2 adults and 2 suitcases, and no more. The room had Air con and it worked very well. We paid 100 Euro, by contacting the hotel direct via email. We did have breakfast one of the mornings we stayed there it cost 10Euro each and consisted of cereals, boiled eggs, toast cheeses, cold meats, yougurt, pastries, and juice. Overall it was ok, and a good price for being so central. 
