<Author>crenzu01
<Content>You can't find a better bargain in Paris The Hotel Louvre Forum made our stay in Paris so much more enjoyable. I am a college student and recently spent 5 days in paris with my mom. We found the Louvre Forum through great reviews, and were not disappointed at all. The hotel has great rates and is one the largest rooms I've stayed in Europe. The staff was so friendly and always willing to help us with directions, what to do, and where to go. The man who sits at the desk during the day is so nice and knows everything there is to know about the surrounding area. The cafe on the corner was a great spot for breakfast and drinks, and though les halles is a little hard to get around it was a great place to be in the city. You are just minutes away from the Louvre and most of the other sites are within walking distance. If not, the metro is also right by the hotel. Overall, you can't ask for better value and better accommodations right in the heart of Paris. I would recommend this hotel to any and everyone! 
