<Author>dcmehany
<Content>fabulous location, decent hotel My husband and I recently stayed at this hotel when on a short trip to Paris with friends. we booked two standard rooms and were overall very pleased with the hotel.Pros:- Fabulous location. Absolutely fabulous. I cannot say enough good about this location. It is within walking distance from two metro stops (one of which is an RER to get to the airport), and to most major attractions. it is on the yellow line, which stops at the arc and notre dame and marais and connects easily to the eiffel tower. We were travelling with a couple that preferred to metro a bit more than we normally do and thus really enjoyed this about the location. It is literally two blocks (small ones) to the louvre and the tuilleries.- Fabulous staff. There are maps at the hotel and the staff speaks excellent english and will help you find anything. They are also quite knowledgeable about costs of things and where to buy museum passes, etc. Additionally, my husband and I forgot which terminal we were leaving out of when we left and the girl at the desk happily called the airport to find out for us. very kind.- comfortable bed. Trust me, you want a comfortable bed when you have been sightseeing the entire day.- great hot water. never seems to run out.- cheap coca cola! as an American, we do crave the odd coke. at 2 euros a bottle, this is cheaper than anywhere but a monoprix!- windows that open. this is nice when you want to get a little air circulating! additionally, the hotel is on a relatively quiet side street, so you could sleep with the window open.- very clean hotel.Cons:- I cannot stress to you how small the rooms are. the couple we were with was quite shocked. I think this hotel room was smaller than the three other hotels I have stayed in Paris. That being said, this hotel was also much cheaper at 100 euro per night.- though the hotel was clean, it was definitely worn about the edges. it could do with some new wallpaper, etc. that being said, the bathroom looked relatively new, as did the bedding.- I think this is normal in european rooms, but they do not change your bedding daily. and one day when they did change our bedding, the merely took the sheet off and just left us the duvet!- the shower is TINY. my husband and I are normal sized (even smaller sized by US standards), and we were quite squished in the shower. just not much room to manuever, etc.- the lift barely fit two people with smallish suitcases. but that is normal and not really a complaint. we did the four of us fit in a few times to ride up and down (though it states it only holds three people). quite humourous.- we only had the hotel breakfast one day, and it was quite late when we did (it was the day we slept in and didn't have breakfast until nearly 9am). we noticed that they had run out of most things and did not replenish. fine if you go at 7am, but for 10 euros, I want the boiled eggs and larger yogurt and bread variety even at 9am!for the price and the location, I would stay here again if travelling with people on a budget. I usually prefer the other eme., but we were travelling with a couple who had never visited paris and wanted to stay centrally. it was an excellent hotel overall. 
