<Content>A reasonable hotel Having read the trip advisor reviews and had fantastic experiences in the past when choosing hotels based on these reviews, we decided to stay at the Louvre Forum. It鈥檚 a very reasonable hotel, but my expectations which were based upon the reviews and my past experiences were probably set to high.The location is excellent with The Louvre  Notre Dame within easy walking distance. Also the Chatelet Les Halles RER Station is close (5 min) and makes the transfer from CDG Airport very simple. There is a bus stop very close (1 min) where you can catch a bus (No 67) to Pagelle for a visit to Sacre Couer and the Montmare district. The hotel itself is OK, no more, no less.Clean but a little bit tired in places.Very friendly  helpful staff.Breakfast is OK with a choice of cereal, breads, cold meat, cheese and fruit, but is probably not worth the 9 Euro鈥檚 price, but I like the convenience of breakfasting in the hotel.The room size was fine for us but perhaps could be considered a little small. The shower was very small, but was clean and had hot water, so again no real problem for us.At the end of a days site seeing, I find it useful to catch up with news and stuff on TV. Unfortunately, there was no English TV available. Although not a big issue when visiting such a lovely city, I have to confess that I will in future always check ahead that any hotel that I book is offering some English channels. If the price were right, I would book this hotel again, however I would definitely shop around first as The Louvre Forum just does not have any wow factor. It鈥檚 an OK place to stay and the friendly staff and location will guarantee you a good visit to Paris. 
